02/05/2004
SPLIT, Croatia -- The commander of the US Navy Sixth Fleet and NATO Joint Headquarters in Lisbon, Vice Admiral Harry Ulrich, met with Croatian Navy commander Rear Admiral Zdravko Kardum on Friday (30 April) in Split to discuss co-operation between the two fleets. 
Officials say such co-operation would contribute to regional peace and the fight against terrorism.
In other news Friday, Croatia and Slovenia opened the modernised international border crossing at Metlika. 
The renovated crossing meets Schengen security and customs standards. 
Total cost of the project was 2.1m euros. 
(HINA, STA - 30/04/04)
